The 2021 Indian Premier League, also known as IPL 14 or, for sponsorship reasons, Vivo IPL 2021,[1] was the fourteenth season of the Indian Premier League (IPL), 
a professional Twenty20 cricket league established by the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) in 2007
It was played in two part.(1)9 April – 2 May (2)19 September – 15 October 2021
Participants:	8 teams
matches played: 60
Champions:	Chennai Super Kings (4th title)
Runners-up:	Kolkata Knight Riders
Player of the series:	India Harshal Patel (RCB) (59 runs and 32 wickets)
Most runs	:India Ruturaj Gaikwad (CSK) (635)
Most wickets	:India Harshal Patel (RCB) (32)
